tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity), suggesting significant renal dysfunction. Blood chloride is mildly elevated. Low HbA1c and HDL, and low total cholesterol are noted. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Findings are consistent with acute or chronic kidney disease; urgent nephrology evaluation is recommended.
